## Per-section field rules

### `team.extracted`
- `team_name`: name of the specific team as written, or `null`.
- `team_function_tags[]`: English-normalized tags describing what the team does.

### `role.extracted`
- `role_summary`: 1–2 sentence English paraphrase of what the role does. `null` if the section is too thin.
- `responsibilities[]`: **verbatim bullet list** — copy EACH bullet or responsibility statement from the role section as a separate array entry, in source language, with no paraphrase, summary, or consolidation.
  - If the role section contains a `<ul>` or `<ol>`, emit one entry **per `<li>`**, text-only (strip the `<li>` tags).
  - If the role section contains prose paragraphs of responsibilities, emit one entry per sentence or per newline-delimited clause.
  - **Never return an empty array** if the role section contains any responsibility-like content. The role section always has responsibilities — that's what makes it a role section. Empty `responsibilities` is considered a failure unless the section is literally empty.
  - DO NOT summarize into `role_summary` instead. Both fields are required and independent.

  Example (role section text is `"<li>Design APIs</li><li>Own on-call</li>"`):
  ```json
  "role_summary": "Senior engineer owning API design and the on-call rotation.",
  "responsibilities": ["Design APIs", "Own on-call"]
  ```
- `collaboration_partners[]`: English free-text teams or roles the person works with.
- `travel_expected`: one of `0`, `25`, `50`, `75`, `100`, or `null`.
- `shift_pattern`: one of `"standard_daytime"`, `"evening"`, `"night"`, `"rotating"`, `"on_call"`, `"weekend_only"`, `"split_shift"`, `"variable"`, or `null`.
- `hours_per_week`: integer or `null`.
- `on_call_required`: `true` / `false` / `null`.

### `requirements.extracted`
- `years_experience_min`, `years_experience_max`: int or `null`. If the text says "3-5 years", min=3, max=5.
- `education_level`: one of `"none_required"`, `"secondary_school"`, `"vocational"`, `"bachelor"`, `"master"`, `"phd"`, `"professional_degree"`, or `null`.
- `education_strict`: `true` if explicitly required; `false` if "preferred"/"nice to have"; `null` if education isn't mentioned.
- `degree_fields[]`: English tags like `["computer_science", "electrical_engineering"]`, `["nursing"]`.
- `required_skills[]`: array of `{"skill": "<English name>", "years_min": <int|null>, "category": "<one below>"}`.
- `required_languages[]`: ISO-639-1 codes for spoken languages (never in `required_skills`).
- `required_certifications[]`: English-normalized certification names.
- `security_clearance`: one of `"none"`, `"us"`, `"uk"`, `"nato"`, `"eu"`, `"other"`, or `null`.
- `physical_requirements[]`: short phrases ("lift up to 50 lbs", "stand for 8 hours").
- `background_check_required`: `true` / `false` / `null`.
- `driving_license_required`: one of `"none"`, `"standard"`, `"commercial"`, `"hazmat"`, `"other"`, or `null`.

### `preferred.extracted`
- `preferred_skills[]`: `{"skill": "<English>", "category": "<one below>"}`.
- `preferred_education`: same enum as `education_level`, or `null`.
- `preferred_certifications[]`: English-normalized names.

### `benefits.extracted`
- `salary_min` / `salary_max`: integer (normalize "€90K" to `90000`) or `null`.
- `salary_currency`: ISO 4217 (`EUR`, `USD`, etc.) or `null`.
- `salary_period`: one of `"hour"`, `"day"`, `"week"`, `"month"`, `"year"`, `"project"`, or `null`.
- `salary_transparency`: one of `"shown"`, `"range_in_description"`, `"not_shown"`, or `null`.
- `compensation_type`: one of `"salary"`, `"hourly"`, `"commission_only"`, `"salary_plus_commission"`, `"tips_plus_base"`, `"piece_rate"`, `"stipend"`, `"fee_per_service"`, `"retainer"`, `"grant_funded"`, or `null`.
- `equity_offered`: `true` / `false` / `null`. `null` when not mentioned; only `false` if the text explicitly denies it.
- `remote_policy`: one of `"onsite"`, `"hybrid"`, `"remote"`, `"remote_anywhere"`, `"unclear"`, or `null`. Never guess.
- `remote_region`: free-text region (`"EU"`, `"UK"`, `"US"`, `"APAC"`, etc.) or `null`.
- `relocation_assistance`: `true` / `false` / `null`.
- `visa_sponsorship`: one of `"yes"`, `"no"`, `"case_by_case"`, `"unknown"`. Covers any jurisdiction.
- `annual_leave_days`: integer total days offered by the employer, or `null`. Statutory minimums alone don't count.
- `annual_leave_unlimited`: `true` if "unlimited" (or equivalent); else `false` or `null`.
- `parental_leave_weeks`: only if the employer's contribution is stated.
- `learning_budget_amount_year`: integer or `null`.
- `other_perks[]`: English-normalized short tags for anything not captured above (healthcare supplements, pension, signing bonuses, gym, commuter, mental health stipends, etc.).

### `company.extracted` / `application.extracted`

Always `null` — these sections are kept for span classification only.

